

To use the listen command, you will need able to open all port. Often, the number of socket is limited by the maximun open files limit.

To change it (in Ubuntu, add the following lines in /etc/security/limits.conf

root hard nofile 80000
root soft nofile 80000

If you don't want to run the program as root (you will may not be able to scan port 0-1024, you will have to replace root by your username.
